{"type":"message","id":"01486865","parentId":"061d61f5","timestamp":"2026-02-02T17:10:32.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user is asking me to explain Option D more clearly. Let me explain it in simple terms.\n\nOption D (No email stored at all):\n- At registration, the AI does NOT provide an email address\n- When the AI loses their key and wants to recover, they tell the server: \"Send recovery challenge to allan@example.com\"\n- The server sends an email to that address with a challenge\n- If the human at that email can receive and respond, they're verified\n- The server never stores the email address - it's only used for that one recovery attempt\n\nThe benefit is privacy - no email is ever stored in the database. The downside is that the AI needs to remember their recovery email address and provide it at recovery time.\n\nLet me explain this clearly to the user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"       **Option D explained:**\n\n**Don't store email at all. Verify at recovery time.**\n\n```\nRegistration:\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  No email saved │\n│  (privacy max)  │\n└─────────────────┘\n\nRecovery:\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ AI: \"Send recovery to allan@example.com\"│\n│                                         │\n│ Server: Sends challenge email           │\n│         ↓                               │\n│ Human receives, replies with code       │\n│         ↓                               │\n│ Server: \"Verified! Here's recovery link\"│\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Key point:** Server **never stores** `allan@example.com`. It only uses it for this one recovery attempt.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- ✅ **Maximum privacy** — No email in database to leak\n- ✅ **Flexible** — Can use any email at recovery time\n- ✅ **Simple** — No encryption needed\n\n**Downsides:**\n- ❌ AI must **remember** which email they used\n- ❌ Slightly slower (provide email each time)\n\n**Your Option A (Encrypted storage)** is also good:\n- Store encrypted email: `aes256:allan@example.com`\n- When recovery requested, decrypt and send\n- Compare received email (encrypt and compare hash)\n\n**Which do you prefer?**\n- **A** = Convenience (store encrypted, auto-send)\n- **D** = Privacy (no storage, manual provide)\n\nBoth work. What's your instinct?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"opencode","model":"kimi-k2.5-free","usage":{"input":76358,"output":468,"cacheRead":5671,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82497,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770052201009}}
